data.value:
# Mulitplayer This uses the friend invite system. To get into a game, you need to do the following:
1. Your network needs to be a Class C IP range 2. Open the games on each PC, then click "Online" 3. The "host" needs to then invite everyone to the lobby. 4. The clients need to accept the invite (F9) 5. Find game and you should all get in.
Notes: Errors are common, you can usualy alt+tab to them and hit space to close them.
"Server Disconnected 57475" is bad news, this requires a total profile reset by deleting all "Plugins\OpenNetStorage\Userfiles" files. Back this up, but there's no guarantee it'll work, and there's not predicting when you'll get it.
# Solo Multiplayer If you're alone in a lobby and want to force start it, type "xpartygo" in the console "~" when a map is found.
You can add bots with "spawnbot #", # being the number of bots. Don't add more than 11, as it can get buggy with that many.
# Zombies Pretty much the same as Multiplayer, though you may need to play around with who's inviting to get it everyone in.
